AGENT AUDIT (unreviewed — treat claims as unverified)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

C++ header: include/emCore/emAnything.h
C++ implementation: src/emCore/emAnything.cpp

C++ public API:
  - class emAnything
    - emAnything()                                     // construct invalid (Data = NULL)
    - emAnything(const emAnything&)                     // copy; increments Data refcount
    - ~emAnything()                                     // decrements Data refcount; deletes if 0
    - emAnything& operator=(const emAnything&)           // copy assignment with refcount management
    Protected:
    - struct AbstractSharedData
      - AbstractSharedData()                            // refcount = 1
      - virtual ~AbstractSharedData()                   // virtual destructor
      - unsigned int RefCount
    - emAnything(AbstractSharedData* data)              // protected ctor from shared data
    - AbstractSharedData* Data                          // pointer to shared data

  - template<class VALUE> class emCastAnything : public emAnything
    - emCastAnything(const VALUE& value)               // wrap a value into emAnything
    - emCastAnything(const emAnything& anything)        // attempt to extract VALUE from emAnything
    - operator const VALUE*() const                     // returns pointer to VALUE or NULL if type mismatch
    Private:
    - struct SharedData : AbstractSharedData
      - SharedData(const VALUE& value)
      - virtual ~SharedData()
      - VALUE Value

  Implementation detail: emCastAnything uses dynamic_cast to check if the AbstractSharedData
  is actually a SharedData<VALUE>, providing type-safe extraction. Copies are implicitly shared
  via refcounted AbstractSharedData.

C++ usage in emCore (68 total occurrences across 5 files):
  - emListBox.h:84: const emAnything& data = emAnything() (parameter with default)
  - emListBox.h:97: const emAnything& data = emAnything() (parameter with default)
  - emListBox.h:118-120: const emAnything& item1data, const emAnything& item2data (compare callback params)
  - emListBox.h:171: emAnything GetItemData(int index) const (return type)
  - emListBox.h:178: void SetItemData(int index, const emAnything& data) (parameter)
  - emListBox.h:274: const emAnything& GetItemData() const (ItemPanelInterface method)
  - emListBox.h:371: emAnything Data (member variable in Item struct)
  - emListBox.cpp:70: AddItem with emAnything data parameter
  - emListBox.cpp:79: InsertItem with emAnything data parameter
  - emListBox.cpp:188-190: DefaultSortFunction with emAnything params
  - emListBox.cpp:350: GetItemData returning emAnything
  - emListBox.cpp:357: SetItemData accepting emAnything
  - emFileSelectionBox.cpp:695,701: emCastAnything<FileItemData>(data) (type extraction)
  - emFileSelectionBox.cpp:967,1074,1184: emCastAnything<FileItemData>(GetItemData()) (type extraction)

Rust equivalents found:
  - emAnything -> Box<dyn Any> (or Option<Box<dyn Any>>)
    - emListBox.rs:234: data: Option<Box<dyn Any>> (Item struct member)
    - emListBox.rs:394: data: Option<Box<dyn Any>> (AddItem parameter)
    - emListBox.rs:413: data: Option<Box<dyn Any>> (InsertItem parameter)
    - emListBox.rs:661: pub fn GetItemData(&self, index: usize) -> Option<&dyn Any>
    - emListBox.rs:666: pub fn SetItemData(&mut self, index: usize, data: Option<Box<dyn Any>>)
  - emCastAnything<T>(anything) -> Any::downcast_ref::<T>() in Rust
    - emPanel.rs:37-45: as_any()/as_any_mut() trait methods for downcasting
  - Implicit sharing (refcounted AbstractSharedData) -> not replicated; Rust uses owned Box<dyn Any>
    - C++ emAnything copies share data (COW-like); Rust Box<dyn Any> is move-only, no sharing

Coverage gaps:
  - Implicit sharing: C++ emAnything copies are cheap (refcount bump); Rust Box<dyn Any> is move-only.
    If the Rust port never copies item data between containers, this is not a functional gap.
  - emCastAnything construction from value: Rust uses Box::new(value) as Box<dyn Any>
  - emCastAnything extraction: Rust uses downcast_ref::<T>() which returns Option<&T>

OPEN QUESTIONS:
  - C++ emAnything supports implicit sharing (multiple emAnything values point to same data). The Rust port uses Box<dyn Any> which is not shared. Is any C++ code path relying on shared-copy semantics of emAnything (beyond just passing it around)?

